03/09/2003
PODGORICA, Serbia-Montenegro -- Montenegrin Prime Minister Milo Djukanovic reiterated Tuesday (2 September) that an independence referendum could be held in three years, as outlined in the Belgrade agreement on the union with Serbia.
He described calls opposing such a referendum as premature, and said the republic remains committed to its union with Serbia.
(B92, BBC, Tanjug, FoNet - 02/09/03)
